This paper deals with probabilistic graphical models and inference, which are common topics in machine learning. Specifically, it focuses on improving the efficiency of stochastic variational inference, which is a popular method for posterior inference in directed graphical models. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.CV (Computer Vision), as these sub-categories often deal with probabilistic models and inference. The sub-categories cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.SY (Systems and Control) are also possible, as they can involve optimization and control problems, which are relevant to the proposed approach.
